This paper is about sentence simplification, which is a natural language processing task. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new model that uses syntactic and lexical constraints, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence, making cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) another likely category. The model is based on a Transformer-based architecture, which is a deep learning model, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) another possible category. The paper also reports empirical results, which suggests that it involves experimentation and evaluation, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) another possible category. Finally, the paper proposes a new approach to sentence simplification, which involves developing a new model, making cs.SD (Sound) another possible category.
